dcterms:description: The Davis kinase dataset includes interactions between a subset of selectivity assays from a kinase protein family and a set of inhibitors, measured using the dissociation constant (Kd) across 442 unique proteins and 68 unique drugs.
dcterms:title: Davis Kinase Dataset

dcterms:description: The KIBA dataset was filtered to yield a total of 229 unique proteins and 2,111 unique drugs, designed to cover the bioactivity of specific kinase inhibitors from various studies, including interactions based on Ki, Kd, and IC50 values.
dcterms:title: KIBA Dataset
